<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued March 14 at 8:10PM CDT until March 14 at 9:00PM CDT by NWS Dallas-Fort Worth</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 900 PM CDT
FOR ROBERTSON...NORTHEASTERN MILAM AND LEON COUNTIES...
At 809 PM CDT, a line of severe storms was located from Buffalo to
Hearne, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Hearne, Buffalo, Franklin, Calvert, Centerville, Jewett, Marquez and
Leona.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
